Insurance and Financial Options

Investing in your dental health

Mint Condition Dental offers several financial options to work with your budget and help you receive the treatments you need. Our dentists and team never want finances to be an obstacle between you and quality dental care.
Learn more about payment and financing options below.

We work with all dental insurances, and accept the following forms of payment:

    • Cash
    • Checks
    • Credit cards (Visa, MasterCard, American Express, and Discover)
    • Dental Savings Plan
Insurance Benefits

We accept most insurance plans that allow you to choose your own dentist. Our team will help process your claim and maximize your benefits. If you have questions if we process your insurance, please ask!

Our in-house membership program! We offer 3 plan options to meet your needs. Save up to $350+ on routine care plus get 25% off all other dental procedures.

Services Include:

  • 2 Professional cleanings
  • 2 Regular exams
  • 2 Fluoride treatment
  • Routine x-rays
  • 1 Emergency exam
  • 25% off other procedures completed at our practice

 

0% Interest In-House Financing

Varidi Dental Payment Plans is a new financing option that we offer to our patients. Varidi gives customers flexible, low-cost payment plans when unexpected expenses happen. The payment plan does not require a credit check. It is simply a monthly withdrawal from a debit card or credit card. The benefits are:

» 100% Approval
» No Credit Check
» Not reported to credit bureaus
» Up to $4,000 payment plan
» No compounding interest - just a simple admin fee
» No application needed
» Payments can be spread out over two years

Care Credit

We work with a third-party financing company to help you finance you and your family’s dental care if needed. CareCredit can be used as a credit card and allows you to make low monthly payments for any of your dental treatments over a period of time.

With CareCredit, you may be eligible for a low-interest or interest-free financing options within a monthly deferment period. We’ve partnered with CareCredit to offer 6-month no-interest and low-interest loans.

You can easily apply for CareCredit online or with one of our team members at our office and find out if you’ve been approved immediately.
